            <h2>Summer Camp Safety Tips</h2>
            <h3>Summer camp vacations are great!</h3>
            <h3>But don’t forget to stay safe!</h3>
            <list display="v" type="numbered">
                <li>
                    <p>Don’t bring <droppable id="droppable_1" example="y">snacks</droppable> or candy into your tent. (Bugs and other animals like these.)</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>When it’s <droppable id="droppable_2">sunny</droppable>, wear a <droppable id="droppable_3">hat</droppable>. Take a water bottle and drink a lot of water.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Use <droppable id="droppable_4">sunblock</droppable>. Put it on your face, neck, and ears!</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Always wear <droppable id="droppable_5">shoes</droppable> so that you don’t cut your feet on stones.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Be <droppable id="droppable_6">careful</droppable> with camp fires.</p>
                </li>
            </list>
        </block>
    </main>
